 Johnson]] (D)\n| Resigned March 4, 1862.\n| colspan=2 | Vacant thereafter\n\n|-\n| [[List of United States Senators from Rhode Island|Rhode Island]] (1)\n| nowrap {{Party shading/Republican}} | [[James F. Simmons]] (R)\n| Resigned August 15, 1862.<br/>Successor was elected.\n| nowrap {{Party shading/Republican}} | [[Samuel G. Arnold]] (R)\n| December 1, 1862\n\n|-\n| [[List of United States Senators from New Jersey|New Jersey]] (1)\n| nowrap {{Party shading/Democratic}} | [[John R. Thomson]] (D)\n| Died September 12, 1862.<br/>Successor was appointed.\n| nowrap {{Party shading/Republican}} | [[Richard S. Field]] (R)\n| November 21, 1862\n\n|-\n| [[List of United States Senators from Oregon|Oregon]] (2)\n| nowrap {{Party shading/Democratic}} | [[Benjamin Stark]] (D)\n| Retired September 12, 1862, upon election of a successor.\n| nowrap {{Party shading/Democratic}} | [[Benjamin F. Harding]] (D)\n| September 12, 1862\n\n|-\n| [[List of United States Senators from Maryland|Maryland]] (3)\n| nowrap {{Party shading/Democratic}} | [[James Pearce]] (D)\n| Died December 20, 1862.<br/>Successor was appointed.\n| nowrap {{Party shading/Unionist}} | [[Thomas H. Hicks]] (U)\n| December 29, 1862\n\n|-\n| [[List of United States Senators from Indiana|Indiana]] (1)\n| nowrap {{Party shading/Unionist}} | [[Joseph A. Wright]] (U)\n| Retired January 14, 1863, upon election of a successor.\n| nowrap {{Party shading/Democratic}} | [[David Turpie]] (D)\n| January 14, 1863\n\n|-\n| [[List of United States Senators from New Jersey|New Jersey]] (1)\n| nowrap {{Party shading/Republican}} | [[Richard S. Field]] (R)\n| Retired January 14, 1863, upon election of a successor.\n| nowrap {{Party shading/Democratic}} | [[James W. Wall]] (D)\n| January 14, 1863\n|}\n\n=== House of Representatives ===\n<!--\nSorted Chronologically by date of vacancy\n-->\n{{See also|List of special elections to the United States House of Representatives}}\n{{Ordinal US Congress Rep}}\n\n|-\n| {{ushr|Colorado Territo