{"title_page": "United States congressional delegations from New York", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n[[Image:New York Congressional Districts, 113th Congress.tif|600px|thumb|right|<center>'''New York's congressional districts since 2013'''<ref>{{cite web|title=The national atlas|url=http://nationalatlas.gov/printable/congress.html|publisher=nationalatlas.gov|accessdate=February 2, 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222045635/http://www.nationalatlas.gov/printable/congress.html|archivedate=February 22, 2014}}</ref></center>]]\n\nThese are tables of [[Congress of the United States|congressional]] delegations from [[New York (state)|New York]] to the [[United States House of Representatives]] and the [[United States Senate]].\n\n==House of Representatives==\n{{Main|List of United States Representatives from New York}}\n\n===Current representatives===\nThis is a list of members of the current New York delegation in the U.S. House, along with their respective tenures in office, district boundaries, and district political ratings according to the [[CPVI]]. The delegation has a total of 27 members, including 21 [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democrats]] and 5 [[Republican Party (United States)|Republicans]]. One seat is currently vacant.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- valign=bottom\n! rowspan=2 | Dist<br/>rict\n! colspan=3 | Member\n! colspan=2 | District\n|-\n! Representative<br/>(Residence)\n! Party\n! Incumbent time in office\n! [[CPVI]]\n! Map\n\n|-\n! {{ushr|NY|1|R}}\n| [[File:Lee Zeldin new official portrait.jpg|100px]]<br/>[[Lee Zeldin]]<br/>([[Shirley, New York|Shirley]])\n| {{Party shading/Republican}} | [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n| January 3, 2015\n| {{Party shading/Republican}} data-sort-value=5 | R+5\n| [[File:New York US Congressional District 1 (since 2013).tif|400px|]]\n\n|-\n! {{ushr|NY|2|R}}\n| [[File:Peterking.jpg|100px]]<br/>[[Peter T. King|Peter King]]<br/>([[Seaford, New York|Seaford]])\n| {{Party shading/Republican}} | [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n| January 3, 1993\n| {{Party shading/Republican}} data-sort-value=3 | R+3\n| [[File:New York US Congressional District 2 (since 2013).tif|400px|]]\n\n|-\n! {{ushr|NY|3|R}}\n| [[File:Thomas Suozzi official photo.jpg|100px]]<br/>[[Thomas Suozzi]]<br/>([[Glen Cove, New York|Glen Cove]])\n| {{Party shading/Democratic}} | [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n| January 3, 2017\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} data-sort-value=-1 | D+1\n| [[File:New York US Congressional District 3 (since 2013).tif|400px|]]\n\n|-\n! {{ushr|NY|4|R}}\n| [[File:Kathleen Rice official photo (cropped).jpg|100px]]<br/>[[Kathleen Rice]]<br/>([[Garden City, New York|Garden City]])\n| {{Party shading/Democratic}} | [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n| January 3, 2015\n| {{Party shading/Democratic}} data-sort-value=-4 | D+4\n| [[File:New York US Congressional District 4 (since 2013).tif|400px|]]\n\n|-\n! {{ushr|NY|5|R}}\n| [[File:Gregory Meeks, Official Photo.jpg|100px]]<br/>[[Gregory Meeks]]<br/>([[Queens]])\n| {{Party shading/Democratic}} | [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n| February 3, 1998\n| {{Party shading/Democratic}} data-sort-value=-37 | D+37\n| [[File:New York US Congressional District 5 (since 2013).tif|400px|]]\n\n|-\n! {{ushr|NY|6|R}}\n| [[File:Grace Meng Official Congressional Photo.jpg|100px]]<br/>[[Grace Meng]]<br/>([[Queens]])\n| {{Party shading/Democratic}} | [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n| January 3, 2013\n| {{Party shading/Democratic}} data-sort-value=-16 | D+16\n| [[File:New York US Congressional District 6 (since 2013).tif|400px|]]\n\n|-\n! {{ushr|NY|7|R}}\n| [[File:Nydia Vel\u00e1zquez.jpg|100px]]<br/>[[Nydia Vel\u00e1zquez]]<br/>([[Brooklyn]]/[[Queens]])\n| {{Party shading/Democratic}} | [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n| January 3, 1993\n| {{Party shading/Democratic}} data-sort-value=-38 | D+